# AI Agent Guide

This catalog includes built-in support for AI coding assistants like Claude Code.

## Quick Start

When working with an AI assistant in this project, you can use these slash commands:

### Development Workflow

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `/add-property` | Add a new property to {{.EntityName}} |
| `/add-artifact` | Add a new artifact type |
| `/add-provider` | Add a new data provider |
| `/regenerate` | Regenerate code from catalog.yaml |
| `/fix-build` | Diagnose and fix build errors |
{{.ArtifactSection}}
### Testing & Debugging

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `/run-local` | Start the server locally |
| `/test-api` | Generate curl commands to test API endpoints |
| `/seed-data` | Populate sample test data |

## File Structure

```
{{.CatalogName}}/
├── CLAUDE.md                 # Main project context for AI agents
├── .claude/
│   ├── commands/             # Slash command definitions
│   └── skills/               # Detailed skill instructions
└── docs/
    └── ai-agent-guide.md     # This file
```

## How It Works

1. **CLAUDE.md** - Provides project context, architecture overview, and quick reference
2. **Slash Commands** (`.claude/commands/`) - Short prompts that invoke skills
3. **Skills** (`.claude/skills/`) - Detailed step-by-step instructions with code snippets

When you use a slash command like `/add-property`, the AI reads the corresponding skill file and follows the instructions.

## Regeneration

These files are auto-generated by `catalog-gen`:

- Created during `catalog-gen init`
- Updated during `catalog-gen generate`

Do not edit these files manually - your changes will be overwritten.

